<content>
    <para id="id1170744463884">While lithium shows many properties that are clearly consistent with its position in Group 1, it also has key differences to the other alkali metals. In fact, in many ways it is more similar to its diagonal neighbor magnesium (Mg) than the other Group 1 metals. </para>
    <section id="id1170744257047">
      <title>Charge/radius</title>
      <para id="id1170745328715">The ionic radius for the +1 cation of lithium is very small in comparison with its next highest homolog, sodium (<link target-id="id1170746795191"/>). This results in a correspondingly high value for the charge density (z/r). As may be seen from <link target-id="id1170746795191"/> the charge density for lithium is significantly higher than that of its Group 1 relations. </para>
